dv> and B/f_max. Our simulations naturally\nexplain the observed (i) anticorrelation of the solar wind speed and the\ncoronal temperature and (ii) larger amplitude of the Alfvenic fluctuations in\nthe fast winds. In Appendix, we also explain our implementation of the outgoing\nboundary condition of the MHD waves with some numerical tests.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 31 Oct 2005 22:06:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 24 Nov 2005 07:01:53 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 1 Dec 2005 05:38:33 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 26 Jan 2006 13:44:21 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Thu, 9 Feb 2006 04:43:52 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Mon, 17 Apr 2006 03:31:57 GMT"},{"version":"v7","created":"Fri, 12 May 2006 05:50:37 GMT"},{"version":"v8","created":"Mon, 22 May 2006 03:27:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-24"}
